summary: I use a bit of a range of different media at uni for a range of different stuff but what I tend to default back too and what I'd...
body:
I’m a broke ass art student and I’m thinking of opening comissions

I use a bit of a range of different media at uni for a range of different stuff but what I tend to default back too and what I’d most likely offer is tonal pencil portraits.

Here are some examples of my more elaborate pieces in that style (each of these two images is equivalent of an A2 piece of paper and drawn entirely in pencil).

If I were to do commissions similar to this they would most likely be on a smaller scale and therefore a little less detailed. If I do it, would people be interested and if so what kind of price would they be willing to pay?

Or I could open up slots to do tarot readings like every gay on this site but I might have to buy I knew deck for that cos my old one is well and truly post
